Package com.example.gamecardinal.api

Class ApiClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.gamecardinal.api.ApiClient
  • public class ApiClient
extends java.lang.Object
    Singleton class used to access the network RequestQueue. It is through this class that any and all network requests for GameCardinal should be added.

    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        public static ApiClient getInstance​(Context context)
        Returns the ApiClient singleton for access. If the ApiClient has not yet been instantiated, this method creates it for us automatically.
        Parameters:
        context - the current application context
        Returns:
        access to the ApiClient singleton

      • getRequestQueue

        public com.android.volley.RequestQueue getRequestQueue()
        Returns the RequestQueue managed by this ApiClient for the application. If a RequestQueue has not yet been instantiated, this method will create one for the ApiClient.
        Returns:
        the RequestQueue of this ApiClient

      • addToRequestQueue

        public <T> void addToRequestQueue​(com.android.volley.Request<T> req)
        Adds a request to the current RequestQueue managed by the ApiClient. If the RequestQueue does not yet exist, one is created via a method call before subequently adding the request.
        Type Parameters:
        T - generic type of the request
        Parameters:
        req - the network request to add to the ApiClient's RequestQueue
